ars. Each selection is preceded by a short introduction and biography of the writer. For English-language readers who are familiar with the work of Italo Calvino and Umberto Eco, this collection presents an opportunity to acquaint themselves with the work of other important contemporary Italian writers of fiction.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 0aItalian fictiony21st centuryvTranslations into English. 0aShort stories, ItalianvTranslations into English. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh1 aBompiani, Ginevra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBufalino, Gesualdo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCapriolo, Paola, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCelati, Gianni, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aConsolo, Vincenzo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFerrucci, Franco, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiudice, Daniele Del, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLuca, Erri De, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMalerba, Luigi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aManganelli, Giorgio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aOrtese, Anna Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPasinetti, Pier Maria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRamondino, Fabrizia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRiva, Massimo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRomano, Lalla, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTabucchi, Antonio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.l